                    <fixVersion>1.8.0</fixVersion>
                                    <component>java</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>5</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13043149" author="scott_carey" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 00:10:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch with a command line Tool class for recovering data from a corrupt AvroDataFile.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can recover most valid records from blocks that contain corrupt records.  It can&apos;t deal with various sync marker or header corruption cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13043150" author="scott_carey" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 00:12:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is ready for inclusion, but wanted to provide the work in progress as a starting point or reference for others.  It needs some cleanup, documentation, and unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will not be working on refining this further at this time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14180055" author="tomwhite" created="Wed, 22 Oct 2014 15:34:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I recently used this tool to recover a corrupt Avro file, so it would be good to move it along and make it available in a release. Here&apos;s a patch based on Scott&apos;s that adds a test to exercise the tool for one file with a corrupt block and one with a corrupt record. (For a corrupt block none of the records are recoverable, whereas in the case of a corrupt record all of the previous records in the block are recoverable.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This depends on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1596&quot; title=&quot;Cannot read past corrupted block in Avro data file&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1596&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1596&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to run.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14183138" author="cutting" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2014 17:53:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 This looks good.  We should probably add some javadoc for the new getBlockSize() method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14214767" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 16:04:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1640179 from tomwhite@apache.org in branch &apos;avro/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1640179&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1640179&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-834&quot; title=&quot;Data File corruption recovery tool&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-834&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-834&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Java: Data File corruption recovery tool. Contributed by scottcarey and tomwhite.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14214774" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 16:08:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1640181 from tomwhite@apache.org in branch &apos;avro/branches/branch-1.7&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1640181&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1640181&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Merge -r 1640178:1640179 from trunk to branch. Fixes: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1596&quot; title=&quot;Cannot read past corrupted block in Avro data file&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1596&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1596&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-834&quot; title=&quot;Data File corruption recovery tool&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-834&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-834&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Java: Data File corruption recovery tool. Contributed by scottcarey and tomwhite.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14214778" author="tomwhite" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 16:10:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added some javadoc to getBlockSize(), and committed this. Thanks for the contribution Scott!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14214815" author="hudson" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 16:35:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in AvroJava #499 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/AvroJava/499/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/AvroJava/499/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-834&quot; title=&quot;Data File corruption recovery tool&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-834&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-834&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Java: Data File corruption recovery tool. Contributed by scottcarey and tomwhite. (tomwhite: rev 1640179)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/avro/trunk/CHANGES.txt&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/avro/trunk/lang/java/avro/src/main/java/org/apache/avro/file/DataFileStream.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/avro/trunk/lang/java/tools/src/main/java/org/apache/avro/tool/DataFileRepairTool.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/avro/trunk/lang/java/tools/src/main/java/org/apache/avro/tool/Main.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/avro/trunk/lang/java/tools/src/test/java/org/apache/avro/tool/TestDataFileRepairTool.java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
